I've visited this page: <a href="http://www.musiktreff.info/modules.php?name=Your_Account" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://www.musiktreff.info/modules.php?name=Your_Account</a> and haven't found anything suspicious. I'd like to ask you to bother the server admin, let he check the error log, maybe it contains some hints.
<br />

<br />
Meanwhile, it's possible to make a few tests.
<br />

<br />
1) Ask user to enter &quot;test&quot; as Benutzername, &quot;test&quot; as Passwort, submit the login form. Does he get a white page or error message &quot;Login fehlerhaft&quot;?
<br />

<br />
2) Ask user to answer _wrong_ to the question. Does he get a white page or the form again?
<br />

<br />
3) Temporary switch off the protection and ask the user to login. Is it possible?<br />_________________<br />Oleg Parashchenko, bbAntiSpam
